The party is not always written with red numbers
In Hungary the law precisely defines the days that are written with red numbers in the calendar and has already become a widespread practice that around the holidays - that the next year will be less - the working days are reorganized.
Not even in the EU or in North America are the parties united.
Hungarian laws make a difference between national parties, state parties and holidays.
The festive days are mainly related to religious festivals and historical ephemeris.
We celebrate the New Year too: both the last day of the old year, and the first day of the new year is festive - the latter especially so that those who have spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have eleven parties written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national festival on 15 March in memory of the 1848 and 23 October revolution, a commemorative day of the 1956 revolution.
On 20 August we celebrated the foundation of the State, on 1 May the festival of work, on 1 and 2 November we remind our family and friends who died.
In addition, in our country are two-day parties the Easter of Resurrection, Pentecost and Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays rarely coincide with a weekend, so it is often made a bridge when before or after the party there is only one working day.
In exchange for the extended weekends so, during the previous Saturdays you cannot be absent from work or school.
It is the Minister of Labour who regulates in his specific decree when it is necessary to work exactly in exchange for the day directly preceding or after the feast.
This legal rule is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for employees and public servants.
It is not mandatory for companies and service institutions that, because of their role, work continuously even during holidays.
This year the order of work may be altered only around the parties of the end of the year: from 24 December virtually stops life in the country, because according to experiences, most people "make bridges" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their holidays during these days.
Next year several of our parties will coincide with middle or weekend, so there will be fewer changes in working days than this year.
The agenda will first be modified around the work party so that, for four successive days, workers can rest.
Saturday, April 26 will be a working day, so that Friday, May 2, will be a festive day.
The other change relates to the party on October 23rd: Saturday, October 18, will have to work instead of Friday 24.
On the other hand, the anus that comes during the end-of-year party can rest, since from 24 December it will not be worked in almost any part of the year, even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
